OL,7,FIn a social media post, the writer
OL,8,Fargued: "It is impossible to
OL,9,Faccurately describe or tackle the
OL,10,Freality of violence and sexual
OL,11,Fviolence committed against women and
OL,12,Fgirls, or address the current assault
OL,13,Fon women's and girls' rights, unless
OL,14,Fwe are allowed to call a man a man."
OL,16,FCriticising the new laws, she insisted
OL,17,Fthat the "legislation is wide open to
OL,18,Fabuse by activists who wish to silence
OL,19,Fthose of us speaking out about the
OL,20,Fdangers of eliminating women's and
OL,21,Fgirls' single-sex spaces".
