OL,7,F"If you're thinking about making a
OL,8,Fvexatious complaint, if you're
OL,9,Fthinking about making a complaint and
OL,10,Fthere's no merit in that, then do know
OL,11,Fthat the police will take that serious
OL,12,Fin terms of tackling vexatious
OL,13,Fcomplaints and so I would urge you not
OL,14,Fto do it."
OL,16,FThe First Minister has repeatedly said
OL,17,Fthere is "disinformation" being spread
OL,18,Fabout the Bill and what it entails,
OL,19,Fclaiming there is a "triple lock" of
OL,20,Fprotection for speech.
